Sentencas: Single-phase silver (Ag)-doped La0.85-xSr0.15AgxFeO3-delta (x = 0-0.05) materials (LSAF) were synthesized by wet synthesis route and calcined at 800 degrees C in air.
Titulo: Facilitating oxygen reduction by silver nanoparticles on lanthanum strontium ferrite cathode

Sentencas: The materials exhibited no thermal degradation in Ar and synthetic air below sintering temperature at 1200 degrees C of the cathode for solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Facilitating oxygen reduction by silver nanoparticles on lanthanum strontium ferrite cathode

Sentencas: Exsolution of Ag nanoparticles from the perovskite lattice at 420 degrees C in reducing 5% H-2/N-2 was investigated, and electrocatalytic activity of the cathodes towards oxygen reduction reaction for solid oxide fuel cells was demonstrated.
Titulo: Facilitating oxygen reduction by silver nanoparticles on lanthanum strontium ferrite cathode

Sentencas: Scanning electron microscopy confirmed exsolution of Ag nanoparticles with increased effective surface area, and the particles were distributed with a good contact on the surface of the perovskite.
Titulo: Facilitating oxygen reduction by silver nanoparticles on lanthanum strontium ferrite cathode

Sentencas: Electrochemical performance of novel materials was tested and compared.
Titulo: Facilitating oxygen reduction by silver nanoparticles on lanthanum strontium ferrite cathode

Sentencas: Enhanced cathode with Ag nanoparticles revealed the area specific resistance of 0.23 and 0.15 omega cm(2) at 800 degrees C in 20% O-2/N-2 before and after Ag exsolution, respectively.
Titulo: Facilitating oxygen reduction by silver nanoparticles on lanthanum strontium ferrite cathode

Sentencas: The area specific resistance of the cathode decreased with Ag exsolution, operation temperature, and increasing oxygen partial pressure.
Titulo: Facilitating oxygen reduction by silver nanoparticles on lanthanum strontium ferrite cathode
